>The British can own single and double barrel shotguns, but only if 
>they're licensed and registered and they can only use birdshot.  If 
>you take a look at British gun magazines, you'll see advertisements 
>for really good replica firearms-  They're kind of expensive though.
>
>An unintended consequence to all of this prohibitionist activity, and 
>a not altogether harmful one IMHO, is that the average citizen is 
>losing more and more respect for the government.  And the ultimate 
>unintended consequence is the logical choice between violating the 
>law by owning an illegal fake firearm or by violating the law owning 
>a real one.  Most people will choose owning a real one-
